When discussing wifi, what is:

    an AP
      Acces Point
    a client
      Device connect to the host 
    a bridge
      A network bridge is networking hardware that connects multiple network segments. In the OSI model, bridging is performed in the first two layers, below the network layer (layer 3).
    a repeater
      In telecommunications, a repeater is an electronic device that receives a signal and retransmits it at a higher level or higher power, or onto the other side of an obstruction, so that the signal can cover longer distances.
    ad-hoc mode
      An 802.11 networking framework in which devices or stations communicate directly with each other, without the use of an access point (AP). Ad-hoc mode is also referred to as peer-to-peer mode or an Independent Basic Service Set (IBSS).
    mesh network
      network topology in which each node relays data for the network. 
    war chalking
      drawing of symbols in public places to advertise an open Wi-Fi network
    a rogue AP
      wireless access point installed on a wired enterprise network without authorization from the network administrator. 
